Windows Registry Forensics

	windows Registry:

		Access online -> regedit.exe

			* HKEY_CURRENT_USER -> Current User Settings and data.
			* HKEY_USERS -> All Users Settings and data.
			* HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE -> Contains computer related setting and data for a user.
			* HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT -> Configures Windows Explorer as the way it is also is a combined view of file associations from:
				•	HKLM\Software\Classes (system-wide defaults)
				•	HKCU\Software\Classes (user-specific overrides)
				👉 If a setting exists in both, HKCU (user) takes priority; otherwise it uses HKLM.
			* HKEY_CURRENT_CONFIG -> Contains hardware system startup settings.

		Access offline -> C:\Windows\System32\Config

			*DEFAULT (mounted on HKEY_USERS\DEFAULT)
			*SAM (mounted on HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SAM)
			*SECURITY (mounted on HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Security)
			*SOFTWARE (mounted on HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software)
			*SYSTEM (mounted on HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System)

	Apart from these hives, two other hives containing user information can be found in the User profile directory. For Windows 7 and above, a user’s profile directory is located in C:\Users\<username>\ where the hives are:

		* NTUSER.DAT (mounted on HKEY_CURRENT_USER when a user logs in)
		* USRCLASS.DAT (mounted on HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\CLASSES) -> located in the directory C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\Microsoft\Windows

							---Both are hidden files---

	Apart from these files, there is another very important hive called the AmCache hive. This hive is located in C:\Windows\AppCompat\Programs\Amcache.hve. Windows creates this hive to save information on programs that were recently run on the system.

	Transaction Logs (.LOG, .LOG1, .LOG2)
		•	Act as a journal of registry changes
		•	May contain latest updates not yet written to hives
		•	Stored in: C:\Windows\System32\Config\
		•	Example: SAM.LOG

	Registry Backups (RegBack)
		•	Copies of registry hives (older state)
		•	Stored in: C:\Windows\System32\Config\RegBack\
		•	Typically created every ~10 days
		•	Useful to recover deleted or modified keys
 	
	👉 Use logs for recent changes, backups for previous states

OS Information:
	•	Used to identify Windows version
	•	Useful for compatibility and attack surface analysis
	Location:
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion

Control Sets:
	•	Store system configuration for boot
	•	CurrentControlSet = active configuration (use this for analysis)
	Location:
		SYSTEM\ControlSet001
		SYSTEM\ControlSet002
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet
		SYSTEM\Select\Current
		SYSTEM\Select\LastKnownGood

Computer Name:
	•	Identifies the machine being analyzed
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\ComputerName\ComputerName

Time Zone Information:
	•	Required for accurate timeline analysis
	•	Helps correlate UTC vs local timestamps
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\TimeZoneInformation

Network Interfaces:
	•	Contains IP, DNS, DHCP, subnet details
	•	Helps identify system in network
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Tcpip\Parameters\Interfaces

Past Networks:
	•	Stores previously connected networks
	•	LastWrite time = last connection
	Location:
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\NetworkList\Signatures\Unmanaged
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\NetworkList\Signatures\Managed

Autoruns (Persistence):
	•	Programs executed at user login
	•	Common persistence mechanism
	Location:
		NTUSER.DAT\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run
		NTUSER.DAT\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnce
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnce
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer\Run

Services:
	•	Background system services
	•	Start = 0x02 → runs at boot
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services

SAM Hive (User Information):
	•	Contains user accounts and authentication data
	•	Includes:
		- RID
		- Login count
		- Last login
		- Password details
		- Group membership
	Location:
		SAM\Domains\Account\Users

		Recent Files (RecentDocs):
	•	Tracks recently opened files (MRU order)
	•	Top entry = most recently used
	•	Grouped by file extensions (.pdf, .docx, etc.)
	Location:
		NTUSER.DAT\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\RecentDocs
		NTUSER.DAT\...\RecentDocs\.pdf

Office Recent Files:
	•	Tracks files opened in Microsoft Office
	•	Includes full file paths
	Location:
		NTUSER.DAT\Software\Microsoft\Office\<version>\
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Office\<version>\UserMRU\LiveID_xxx\FileMRU

ShellBags:
	•	Stores folder access and structure information
	•	Can reveal accessed folders (even deleted ones)
	Location:
		USRCLASS.DAT\...\Shell\Bags
		USRCLASS.DAT\...\Shell\BagMRU
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Shell\Bags
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Shell\BagMRU

Open/Save Dialog MRUs:
	•	Tracks files opened/saved through dialog boxes
	•	Useful for application-level file access tracking
	Location:
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Explorer\ComDlg32\OpenSavePIDlMRU
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Explorer\ComDlg32\LastVisitedPidlMRU

Explorer Address/Search:
	•	Tracks typed paths and search queries
	•	Shows user navigation and intent
	Location:
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Explorer\TypedPaths
		NTUSER.DAT\...\Explorer\WordWheelQuery

👉 MRU = Most Recently Used (top = latest activity)

UserAssist:
	•	Tracks GUI-based program execution (via Explorer)
	•	Stores execution count and last run time
	•	Entries are ROT13 encoded
	•	Does NOT track command-line executions
	Location:
		NTUSER.DAT\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\UserAssist\{GUID}\Count

ShimCache (AppCompatCache):
	•	Tracks applications for compatibility purposes
	•	Stores file name, size, and last modified time
	•	Does NOT guarantee execution (use with caution)
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\AppCompatCache

AmCache:
	•	Detailed execution artifact
	•	Stores execution path, SHA1 hash, timestamps
	•	Useful for confirming execution
	Location:
		C:\Windows\AppCompat\Programs\Amcache.hve
		Amcache.hve\Root\File\{Volume GUID}\

BAM / DAM:
	•	Tracks background application execution
	•	Stores full path and last execution time
	•	Per-user (SID-based)
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\bam\UserSettings\{SID}
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\dam\UserSettings\{SID}

👉 Combine multiple artifacts for accurate execution timeline

Device Identification:
	•	Tracks USB devices connected to system
	•	Stores Vendor ID, Product ID, Serial Number
	•	Used to uniquely identify devices
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Enum\USBSTOR
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Enum\USB

Connection Timeline:
	•	Tracks first, last connection and removal times
	Location:
		SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Enum\USBSTOR\<Device>\Properties\{83da6326-97a6-4088-9453-a19231573b29}\####
	
	Values:
		0064 → First connection time
		0066 → Last connection time
		0067 → Last removal time

USB Device Name:
	•	Stores human-readable device name
	•	Correlate with USBSTOR using GUID/Disk ID
	Location:
		SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows Portable Devices\Devices

👉 Combine all keys to reconstruct USB usage timeline